cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it focuses on enabling robotic platforms to perform higher level decision making through the creation of consistent dense maps of the environment. Additionally, the paper addresses the challenge of building scalable maps, which is a common problem in robotics. 

The Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category is also likely as the paper deals with creating 3D maps from visual sensors providing depth information. 

The Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category is a possibility as the paper may involve the use of machine learning techniques for feature-based camera tracking and bundle adjustment. 

The Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category is also possible as the paper deals with higher level decision making for robotic platforms. 

Finally, the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category is a possibility as the paper may involve the use of graphics techniques for visualizing the 3D maps.
